
Some Syntex  short notex for pine script 
ChatGPT
Sure, here are some key syntax notes for Pine Script:

Variables and Data Types:

Declare variables: var_name = expression
Data types: int, float, bool, string, series
Plotting:

Plot a value: plot(value, title="Plot Title", color=color.blue)
Line style: plot(..., style=plot.style_circles)
Conditions and Operators:

Conditional: if condition
Ternary operator: condition ? value_if_true : value_if_false
Logical operators: and, or, not
Moving Averages:

Simple MA: sma = sma(close, length)
Exponential MA: ema = ema(close, length)
Crossovers:

Moving average crossover: crossover(sma1, sma2)
Inputs:

Define input: input(title="Input Name", type=input.integer, defval=14)
Access input: input_var = input_var
Function Declaration:

Declare function: myFunction(arg1, arg2) => ...
Series Operations:

Shift a series: shifted_series = series[1]
Alerts:

Create alert condition: alertcondition(condition, title="Alert Title", message="Alert Message")
Strategy Orders:

Entry: strategy.entry("Long", strategy.long, when=condition)
Exit: strategy.exit("Exit", from_entry="Long", when=condition)
